SIMPLE: antibacterial
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Antibacterial
<hw>An`ti*bac*te"ri*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>killing or inhibiting the growth of
bacteria; -- applied also to serum for protection against bacterial
diseases.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Opposed to the bacterial theory of
disease.</def> <mark>[archaic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Antibacterial</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Antibacterial
<hw>An`ti*bac*te"ri*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>a chemical substance which kills or inhibits the
growth of bacteria.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>antibaryon</ent>⟦br⟧
